			<Comment Bounds="295 480 520 42" Id="28" SizeToText="False" xmlns="http://www.ni.com/MocCommon">
				<p.Text>Top-Level WebVIs usually contain a While Loop that never stops so that they can continue running as long as the web page is open in the user's web browser.</p.Text>
			</Comment>
			<Comment Bounds="75 275 170 90" Id="29" SizeToText="False" xmlns="http://www.ni.com/MocCommon">
				<p.Text>Place setup code before the loop. For example, perform initial data communication and wire the results into the loop.</p.Text>
